thread.title: Oxbridge stuns Heritage-Delray

author: Rick Menning
title: Oxbridge stuns Heritage-Delray
text:
Oxbridge Academy couldn't have scripted a better District 7-3A opening win, their first in school history.
The ThunderWolves came through with a pair of second half touchdowns to defeat American Heritage-Delray, 24-7 on the Stallions field.
Senior running back Travis Homer was huge offensively for Oxbridge (4-1. 1-0 in district) with 158 yards on 36 carries.
Leading 10-7 at halftime, the ThunderWolves cushioned their advantage when, on fourth and 8 from the Heritage 29 quarterback Angelo Navaroli found Trey Green in the end zone for a 17-7 advantage. Traivon Leonard's 21 yard interception return with two minutes left iced the game for Oxbridge.
Devin Singletary led American Heritage-Delray (3-2. 0-1) with 67 yards on 16 carries.
